-- Ukraine to Get $14.8 Billion From IMF in Deal Conditional on Deficit Cuts
-- Chris Kirkham
-- 2010-07-03T12:08:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/ukraine-to-get-14-8-billion-from-imf-in-deal-conditional-on-deficit-cuts.html

          
          
             The International Monetary Fund
announced a new staff-level agreement for Ukraine worth $14.9
billion. Under the terms of the agreement, the government must
achieve a budget deficit of 5.5% of gross domestic product this
year and 3.5 percent next year, the IMF said in an e-mailed
statement today. The government must also ensure the countryâ€™s
banks are sufficiently capitalized and must undertake reforms in
the energy industry, the IMF said.  
